713598f-a.text:
52nd Street, north side, west from 73 East 52nd Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Park Ave. April 3, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

722248f-a.text:
Park Avenue, north on east side, from 52nd Street. The first building at the right is the Montana Apartments, built in 1912 on the site of the old Steinway factory. The N.E. corner of 53rd Street is new, about 1925. 383 Park Avenue, just above it, was built in 1911 and is now oldest building in the block. Further north No. 441, the small dark building on the N.E. corner of 56th Street (about 1880) contrasts with the new Ritz Tower Apartment Building ( t 57th Street, erected 1927. October 28, 1930.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

722249f-a.text:
Park Avenue, north from 52nd Street. The Racquet and Tennis Club occupies the block in the west side between 52nd and 53rd Street. To the right of it is just a glimpse of the Fuller Building Tower at Madison Avenue and 57th Street. On the west side of the Avenue the Ritz Tower rises at 57th Street. Careful comparison of Galloway's photograph of the identical ones shown in the earlier picture. The small apartment house (No. 441) on the N.E. corner of 56th street is also an old building. 1932.

Ewing Galloway.

722250f-a.text:
Park Avenue, north from East 52nd Street, showing an early view of this thoroughfare prior to the enclosure of the railroad tracks shown. At the right is the Steinway Piano factory at the S. E. corner of 53rd Street. The fenced lot on the left is at the N. W. corner of 52nd St.
About 1900
